The paper deals with the problem of forecasting high dimensional time series using matrix factorization techniques. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data science, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
